<br>
He had been working on the new spell and had failed.<br>
<br>
&quot;I work and I slave and what do I get&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know master&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I get you... you shambling heap of bones&quot; he cried.<br>
<br>
&quot;Of course master&quot; Jobartik walked to his side feet clicking on the stone floor.<br>
<br>
&quot;Get away from me you pile of rot, go find me new components&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes master&quot;  and it shambled off down the stairs.<br>
<br>
Maxamillian slumped down in one of his studies plush chairs and tried to visualize the casting and what went wrong.  He had learned of the ability to summon and enslave specters to the summoners will from an anchient text he aquired.  The cost in platinum had been staggering but the gains would be well worth it.<br>
<br>
He visualized the power of the powerfull undead and the prestige it would bring him and the respect it could harness.  He pictured arriving at the arcanum in Freeport for the annual Festival of Magiks with his new servant;  he pictured the mixed expressions of awe and fear it would  garner and he smiled.<br>
<br>
Jobartik clicked back into the chamber.  &quot;Master we are out of Runes&quot; <br>
<br>
Max sighed a heavy breath &quot;Then we will leave in the morn for Antonica, time grows short and I must have this new servant&quot;<br>
<br>
to be continued... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/unazule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nazule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/29/01 3:27:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hallowed Halls</span><hr size=1> The strench of death and decay filtered up into the mess.  Those here trying to eat were hard pressed to get the intense odor.  The had been dealing with this for the past three days not for lack of action;  they had sent a porter to the galley to find the source of the odor and dispose of it.  He never returned.  They sent an ensine to find the missing lad and at last deal with the offensive odor;  he too did not return.<br>
They were about to send a third lad to find the truth behind the smell and the missing ensine and porter, when they heard the ear spliting wail.  They grabbed weapons and tried to enther the hold but the door was barred and even with the combined strength of six burly sailors it would not give.  <br>
The stood around the door discussing what to do next some suggested getting axes and breaking down the portal but even as they spoke a mist was forming around their legs.<br>
The mist seemed to animate in the fresh ocean air and take on claw like fingers.<br>
The two sailors nearest the portal screamed in terror as the talon like mist wrapped around their legs.  They howled an unearthly scream of pain and fear which became high pitched and distant as the others watched rivited in horror.<br>
The crowed backed away as the screams finaly stopped and the sailors fell forward with a lifless thud.<br>
When finally the mists receaded back beyond the portal two of the braver sailors moved too their fallen comrads.  They turned them over to discover the bodies withered and dry,  looking more like mummies of a thousand years than the living breathing men they had been just a short time before.<br>
They had burried the men at sea immediatly and ordered no one go near the hold for the remaineder of the journey to Odus.<br>
Deep in the dark of the hold he smiled well fed and now with the privacy he required for the remaineder of this trip he dreamed of the storm to come.<br>
<br>
