<br>
&quot;So this is home&quot; she mused. The cat no longer rode on her shoulders after being evicted from its perch days before.  It now slinked through the dense underbrush in search nightcrawlers and other suitable prey.<br>
<br>
Gahhl nodded causing a small shower of sweat to fall from his brow. There was a loud snapping of branches and a flurry of activitie to his right.  Bouncer Hurd stormed out of the forest and charged towards her.  She was about to leap into the underbrush to skirt out of the rampaging ogres way when fire exploded in her skull.  The world grew dizzie and dark she looked up at Gahhl through fuzzy eyes and heard him say.<br>
<br>
&quot;You's don't touch me fud, me pickles her gud&quot;<br>
<br>
She slipped into darkness with the image of Gahhl standing over her his wicked blade drawn reaching for her.<br>
<br>
<br>
