<br>
Yes he decided she was pure excitement.  Dinner passed with a series of verbal jousts fiegnts and riposts and he was sure somehow he'd won or at least not let too much slip.  He packed his gear in silence wondering if sometime in the future he would perhaps return here and talk more with Najena.  He smiled inwardly and motioned Gobartik to follow.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/unazule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nazule</A> at: 11/14/01 8:54:07 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/unazule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nazule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/14/01 9:07:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hallowed Halls</span><hr size=1> Gahhl sat staring down at the smooth white object.  He ran his hands slowly across it's surface carressing it as a man would his lover.<br>
She had been watching him for the over an hour wondering what it was that held him in such a thrawl.  She had made many attempts at getting his attention and every time she had been undeniably ignored.  Happily the time spent camped here had brought her joy back and the black cat purred contently under her gentle touch.<br>
<br>
He stood suddenly and moved to the edge of the fire's light.  <br>
&quot;I must travel to a city in Odus will you come with me&quot;  he sounded unsure of himself something she had not seen before.<br>
&quot;I would love to go,  it will be nice to be in a city that doesnt know me&quot;. she replied.<br>
&quot;You will have to arrange passage and a way to get me on board without them knowing&quot;<br>
&quot;Hey now you're talking my specialty, rest assured the world of man I know.  We will need to travel to Qeynos it is the only port with a trade route to Odus that I know of&quot;.<br>
&quot;I know the way, come let us head north to the pass through the Rathe mountains&quot;<br>
<br>
They packed in silence and walked off into the night.<br>
<br>
<br>
Across the sea a ship floated into harbour,  it was deserted, save for corpses...<br>
<br>
