<br>
I do....<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The journey across the sea was a saga of rolling swells and howling winds.  Erud's crossing was not a kind passage in the late of the season;  storms frequenting the tiny cutter leaving all hands in a foul mood.  Deep in the bowels of the ship a large crate filled with dried foods shifted as its crampted passenge stirred.  Gahhl had been in this box for nearly a week and his patience was growing as thing as his food supply.  He bit into a half rotted angel fruit relishing the taste and the added protien the melie worm would provide when he heard a noise.  Leaning close to the wall he could make out only the loudest of sounds as the seas constant crashing would drown out all other.  <br>
There came a light rap, then a second and three more in rapid succession, it was the signal from his traveling companion.<br>
<br>
&quot;We are nearing Odus,  be ready to be moved at first light&quot; she said not bothering to whisper.<br>
<br>
&quot;What first light,  I can see nothing in here&quot;. he shot back.<br>
<br>
She sighed &quot; I will come and rap once more just before we enter the port&quot;.<br>
<br>
The night passed uneventfully and Gahhl was looking forward to the fresh air and open road.  The rapping came as expected but something was amiss,  he could sense it in the actions he heard from above.<br>
<br>
&quot;There is a warship approaching us&quot; she whispered. &quot;The crew is manning battle stations but the ship flies the flag of Erudin. Sit tight I will keep you informed as best I can&quot;. before he could replied he was met by the sound of her departing footsteps.<br>
<br>
The great four masted galleon pulled alongside the cutter fully displaying her many cannons and bastilia a clear show that no resistance would be tollerated.  A magically enhanced voice range out across the sea separating them, It was clear and commanding.<br>
<br>
&quot;Prepare to be Boarded and Searched&quot;.<br>
<br>
Her heart skipped a beat,  how could she stop them from discovering Gahhl.  Surely they would both be doomed if discovered.  As the grappling hooks were secured and the ships were pulling together she slipped back down into the hold.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gahhl.. there is a boarding party coming over to search the ship and they have a mage.  I don't think I can hide you from them&quot;. her voice was shallow and paniced.<br>
<br>
&quot;You are good at weaving stories woman think on your feet and I will provide you with hope&quot; he began chanting and breathing more slowely.<br>
<br>
&quot;What,  give me more than that I...&quot; she stopped short as she heard the booted heals of the Erudin boarding party descending into the hold.<br>
<br>
&quot;Who is that?&quot; a tall darkskinned man in scale armor spoke and pointed her way.  &quot;Remove her untill our search is compleat&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm not going anywhere.  I'm staying to make sure my goods are not damaged in anyway by your intrusion&quot;. she slipped into her role and hoped for the best.<br>
<br>
&quot;Very well ma'mn, stand aside.  Men leave nothing unchecked and call for the magi&quot;.<br>
<br>
The soldiers moved between the rows of crates opening each one, behind them a grotesque eye appeared floating in the air.  The eye moved in turn to each of the opened crates surveying the contents under magical scrutiny.<br>
They came to the crate holding Gahhl, she closed her eyes;  the crate creeked open.  There was a rush of air as the soldiers all gasped at once calling an alarm and drawing their weapons.  On the foor of the crate was the body of an oger.<br>
The captain rushed forward and cried. &quot;Whats the meaning of this&quot;<br>
&quot;It appears to be a dead oger Captain&quot; a footsolder piped in.<br>
<br>
&quot;I can see that but what is it doing here, who owns this crate&quot; he spat.<br>
<br>
&quot;I do&quot; she replied. Looking now for the first time herself she could see that Gahhl was not breathing and he had arranged his gear like a trophy case.<br>
<br>
&quot;What is this about woman&quot; he turned to her even as the disembodied eye moved to get a better look at the crate.<br>
<br>
&quot;It is a collectors item,  a famous oger warrior being delivered to a powerfull merchant in Erudin. Surely you can see my concern that we not be delayed and it not be damaged&quot;. she was picking up steam now and weaving the tale as she went.<br>
<br>
&quot;Who is the collector?&quot; he replied.<br>
<br>
&quot;I cannot tell you that as I am employed through a contract not directly, suffises to say for the price paid for this shipment I would wager he is a powerfull man&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Magi what say you&quot; he seemed distant for a moment. &quot;That weapon keep it secured, also I will provide and escort for you once you leave the ship&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am to take the body beyond the city proper good Captain will you escort me farther or will my own hired men do from there?&quot; she replied curtly.<br>
<br>
&quot;We will take you to the entrace to the forest, from there you are on your own&quot;.<br>
<br>
She breathed inwardly a huge sigh of relief and looked back one last time at Gahhl lieing there not breathing wondering exactly what was going on.  The crate closed and she ascended to the deck with the rest of the crew and soldiers.<br>
She caught brief stories of a ghost ship and strange deaths in the area the last few weeks accounting for the increased patrols.  She sat and hoped that whatever was the cause would not trouble thier journey further.<br>
